summary: Hewlett-Packard (HP) was an American tech company that made computers, printers, and other tech products. It was started in 1939 by Bill Hewlett and David Packard in a garage in California, which is now a historic landmark. HP grew to be a very successful company, becoming the world's top PC maker for a while. They made things for everyone from regular people to big businesses and governments. In 2015, HP split into two companies: HP Inc. for computers and printers, and Hewlett Packard Enterprise for business services.
title: Hewlett-Packard
